<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 17 at 7:49PM CST  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of west central
Pittsburg County through 815 PM CST...
At 749 PM CST, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 3 miles
south of Stuart, moving northeast at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Savanna...                        Haywood...
Scipio...                         Arpelar...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
